The Federal Executive Council (FEC) yesterday approved N22,449,250,040 billion for contracts in the ministries of Petroleum Resources and Environment. The Minister of State for Petroleum Resources, Chief Timipre Sylva, announced this to State House Correspondents after the weekly virtual FEC meeting presided over by President Muhammadu Buhari at the Presidential Villa in Abuja. Sylva said Council approved N22 billion for the construction of a conference hostel facility for the Nigeria Content Development and Monitoring Board (NCDMB) in Yenagoa, the Bayelsa State capital. He said: “The FEC today approved the award of contract procurement for the provision of a conference hostel facility in Yenegoa, adjacent the Nigerian Content Towers for the sum of N22 billion and it is to be constructed in 24 months.”   Fed Govt: petrol scarcity will linger until full…     Kuje prison: 64 Boko Haram suspects escape after attack     Kuje: Day terrorists wreaked havoc   Giving updates on the rehabilitation of the nation’s refineries, Sylva said the Port Harcourt Refinery will soon become operational, adding that the Dangote Refinery will begin operation in January. Also, Environment Minister Muhammed Abdullahi said FEC awarded the contract for consultancy services and design of a Centre of Excellence for Environmental Restoration with an Integrated Contaminated Soil Management Centre for N449,250,040.50. He said:  “…This centre is very epochal because it is meant to impact, in terms of employment generation, in terms of laboratory tests for land remediation efforts on the site that was contaminated so that it can be made easily cultivatable by the people for their fisheries, for their farming and access to water. “…The award was given to Mr. Scrambucl Limited at the sum of N449,250,040.50. Of course, it is inclusive of 7.5 per cent Value Added Tax (VAT). And it is unexpected that this project will be completed within three months.”